  "texts": [
    "Figure 8:8Figure 8: Circuit that implements the U CSP operation, which prepares an arbitrary n -m qubit state for each setting of an m-qubit control register, with the assistance of O(2 n-m) ancillas that begin and end in |0⟩.",
    "We let M = 2 m and N = 2 n. Note that implementations of LOADF, SPF, and FLAG, given in the appendix, involve O(N) additional unshown ancillae.",
    "We also note that in the actual implementation, one can reduce the first LOADF operation so that it is controlled only by the B register (not on the F register, which is guaranteed to be in the |1 N/M -1 ⟩ state at this stage in the circuit) in order to save a constant depth.",
    "We choose to define the LOADF operator in this way only to avoid another definition of the later LOADF †.",
    "(19), we can now let U d = U d(CSP) U d(SP)."
  ],
